---
description: Python best practices for LMForge
globs: "**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---
Python Conventions:
- Use f-strings for formatting.
- Prefer list/dict comprehensions over loops when readable.
- Always use context managers (with statements) for resources.
- Use dataclasses or Pydantic models for data structures.
- Comprehensive error handling: specific exceptions, meaningful messages.
- Tests: use pytest with factories, mock external services (LLMs, DBs).
- Never use bare except: — always specify exception types.